Propose a reaction pathway for synthesiz.answer:
1. Assemble cubane framework:  
   a. Perform a [2+2] cycloaddition between two ethene equivalents to give bicyclo-[1.1.0]-butane;  
   b. Subject to successive Favorskii rearrangements and intramolecular alkylations to close remaining C–C bonds, affording cubane-1,4-dicarboxylic acid;  
   c. Reduce the diacid to cubane (Zn/Hg, HCl).

2. Protect all C–H bonds by exhaustive fluorination: expose cubane to CoF₃ (350 °C, 1 atm) in a nickel reactor, repeatedly sweeping with F₂/He to replace every hydrogen, yielding perfluorocubane (C₈F₈).

The fully perfluorinated, highly symmetric cage confers exceptional kinetic and thermal stability, allowing the molecule to withstand extreme heat, oxidants and radiation.
